The paper deals with the problem of multiuser MIMO downlink beamforming, which is a topic related to information theory (cs.IT) and networking and internet architecture (cs.NI). The use of the SINR metric and power allocation also suggests that the paper may belong to the signal processing (cs.SI) and machine learning (cs.LG) categories. Finally, the use of multiple antennas and receiver diversity suggests that the paper may also belong to the multimedia (cs.MM) category.
